# CODEOWNERS — require maintainer review on structural files.
#
# These files define how the site is built, deployed, and how content is
# validated. A well-meaning content edit that touches one of them can break the
# whole build (and, without review, block every future deploy). Listing them
# here forces a review from the maintainers team before any change can merge.
#
# Replace @btug-maintainers with your real GitHub team or usernames, e.g.
#   /astro.config.mjs  @alice @bob
# Team handles require the team to have write access to this repository.

# Content schema — a bad schema change breaks every content collection.
/src/content/config.ts        @btug-maintainers

# Build + deploy configuration.
/astro.config.mjs             @btug-maintainers

# CI/CD, governance, and these ownership rules themselves.
/.github/                     @btug-maintainers

# Decap/Netlify CMS config — drives the non-technical editing UI.
/public/admin/config.yml      @btug-maintainers
